{{ja-noun|お|hhira=を}}

# {{lb|ja|obsolete|sort=お}} a small place in the [[mountain]]
# {{lb|ja|obsolete|sort=お}} [[hill]], [[hilltop]]
#: {{RQ:Manyoshu|19|4151}}, text [http://jti.lib.virginia.edu/japanese/manyoshu/Man19Yo.html#4151 here]
#: {{ja-usex|m=今日%之%為%等 思%標%之 足%引%乃 '''峯'''%上%之%櫻 如此%開%尓家里|m_kana=けふ%の%ため%と おもひ%しめ%し あし%ひき%の '''をの'''%へ%の%さくら かく%さき%にけり|今%日のためと思ひて標しあしひきの'''峰'''の上の桜かく咲きにけり|け%ふ の ため と おもひて しめし あしひき の '''を'''のへ の さくら かく さき に けり|rom=kyō no tame to omoite shimeshi ashihiki no '''o'''noe no sakura kaku saki ni keri|For the sake of today's feast I thought and put up a sign. The cherry of the foot-dragging '''hill-tops''' has come to blossom thus.<ref>{{cite-book|1963|Jan Lodewijk Pierson, Jr.|The Manyôśû Translated and Annotated Book XIX|publisher=Brill Archive|page=14}}</ref>|sort=お}}
# {{lb|ja|obsolete|sort=お}} [[peak]], [[ridge]]

{{ja-noun|ね}}

# [[summit]] of a [[mountain]], [[peak]]
#: {{RQ:Manyoshu|14|3515}}, text [http://jti.lib.virginia.edu/japanese/manyoshu/Man14Yo.html#3515 here]
#: {{ja-usex|m=阿我於毛乃 和須礼牟之太波 久尓波布利 '''祢'''尓多都久毛乎 見都追之努波西|m_kana=あがおもの わすれむしだは くにはふり '''ね'''にたつくもを みつつしのはせ|我が面の忘れむしだは国はふり'''嶺'''に立つ雲を見つつ偲はせ|あ が おも の わすれむ しだ は くに は ふり '''ね''' に たつくも を みつつ しのはせ|rom=aga omo no wasuremu shida wa kuni wa furi '''ne''' ni tatsukumo o mitsutsu shinowase|The moment you might forget my face, seeing the clouds overflowing the country and rising on the '''peaks''', think of me!<ref>{{cite-book|1958|Jan Lodewijk Pierson, Jr.|The Manyôśû Translated and Annotated Book XX|publisher=Brill Archive|page=74|}}</ref>}}

{{ja-kanjitab|みね|yomi=k}}
From {{ja-compound|御|み|峰|ね|pos1=honorific prefix|t2=[[peak]]}}<ref name=DJR>{{R:Daijirin}}</ref>, in reference to the {{m|ja|神|tr=kami||[[god]] or [[spirit]]}} at the top of a mountain. Now the standard spelling for a ''[[peak]]''.

Compare {{m|ja|道|tr=michi||[[road]]}}.

{{ja-noun|みね}}

# [[peak]], [[ridge]]
#: '''912''', ''{{w|Kokin Wakashū}}'', poem 365 (also ''{{w|Ogura Hyakunin Isshu|Hyakunin Isshu}}'', poem 16)
#: {{ja-usex|立ち別れいなばの山の'''峰'''に生ふるまつとし聞かば今%帰り来む|たちわかれいなばのやまの'''みね'''におふるまつとしきかばいま%かへりこむ|rom=tachi-wakare Inaba-no-yama no '''mine''' ni ouru matsu to shi kikaba ima kaeri-kon|Even if I depart and go to Inaba Mountain, on whose '''peak''' grow pines, if I hear you pine for me, I will return straightway to you.<ref>{{cite-book|1996|Joshua S. Mostow|Pictures of the Heart: The Hyakunin Isshu in Word and Image|publisher=University of Hawaii Press|isbn=0-8248-1705-2|page=190}}</ref>}}
#: '''912''', ''{{w|Kokin Wakashū}}'', poem 776 (also ''{{w|Ogura Hyakunin Isshu|Hyakunin Isshu}}'', poem 13)
#: {{ja-usex|筑%波%嶺の'''峰'''より落つるみなの川%恋ぞ積もりて淵となりぬる|つく%ば%-ね の '''みね''' より おつる みな-の-がは% こひ ぞ つもりて ふち と なり ぬる|rom=Tsukuba-ne no '''mine''' yori otsuru Minano-gawa koi zo tsumorite fuchi to nari nuru|Falling from the '''ridge''' of high Tsukuba, the Minano River at last gathers itself, like my love, into a deep, still pool.<ref>{{cite-book|1964|Kenneth Rexroth|One Hundred Poems from the Japanese|publisher=New Directions Publishing|isbn=0-8112-0181-3|page=103}}</ref>}}
